Condition : 25 - Landscaping and Ecological Enhancement & Management Plan
Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved plans and set out in the supporting information, a Landscape and Ecological Enhancement and Management Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of any above ground works, excluding demolition. The Plan shall include details of all measures to provide biodiversity gain, including but not limited to:
� details of native and known wildlife friendly planting, including mixed native species hedge and scrub and night scented species;
� details of native and known wildlife friendly planting, including mixed native species hedge and scrub and night scented species;
� details of all biodiverse roofs (including any Biosolar roofs) including details of extensive substrate base, features to be included within the substrate e.g. logs, rope coils, sand, gravel, etc., and details of any seeding/plug plant choice with priority given to wildlife friendly species (in accordance with The Gro Green Roof Code 2021);
� the orientation, target species and location for 3x swift and 1x bat box/brick;
� a bat sensitive post-construction lighting plan to ensure that any lighting will be of a specification that minimises its impacts on bats, onsite habitats and adjacent habitats in accordance with the BCT and ILP 2023 Guidance Note (including having a colour temperature of no more than 3000k, measures to reduce light spill onto vegetated areas as much as possible, no light spill onto the biodiverse roof and bird and bat boxes and no uplighters).
� details on the management to be implemented post-construction shall also be submitted, which shall include management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all hard and soft landscaped areas as well as the above-mentioned measures to provide biodiversity gain.
